This category of Mitigations describes a wide range of strategies and actions aimed at promoting and enhancing green spaces, green infrastructure, and sustainable practices in urban areas. These include measures such as creating and maintaining green spaces, parks, and gardens in urban areas, incorporating green elements in urban planning and design, implementing green infrastructure, retrofitting buildings to be more environmentally friendly, increasing access to and availability of green spaces, promoting nature-based solutions, and advocating for policies and investments that support conservation efforts and mitigate climate change. The focus is on creating equitable access to green areas, improving transportation to green spaces, increasing biodiversity, promoting outdoor activities, and incorporating mental health considerations into urban planning. The aim is to create and enhance green spaces in highly urbanized areas, protect and restore ecosystems, mitigate the effects of climate change, and improve the quality of life for individuals living in urban environments. These Mitigations encompass a variety of approaches and initiatives to promote sustainability and resilience in green building neighborhoods.